Market Data Engineer - RMDS		Hatstand		New York, NY		<div class="rich-text" itemprop="description"><p><strong>Summary </strong></p><p>  </p><p>Hatstand, a Global Financial Consultancy, is working with a large investment bank to provide support for an extensive and diverse Market Data infrastructure.   </p><p>  </p><p><strong>Responsibilities include:</strong> </p><p>  </p><p>Seeking a Market Data Infrastructure Engineer whose responsibilities will include answering support calls; Tier 3 desktop escalations raised through numerous media channels, as well as undertaking engineering and deployment tasks for the infrastructure itself. </p><p>  </p><p>Ability to work confidently in a Linux<strong> </strong>environment, at minimum; Wintel/Windows a plus.  Ability to quickly identify and diagnose problems with the infrastructure and to rapidly deploy fixes is paramount. This will involve the ability to use Thomson Reuters’ diagnostics tools to view the health of the RMDS system. </p><p>  </p><p>Writing utilities or scripts in either platform, or in Perl, for both, to automate tasks, would be a plus but is not required. </p><p>  </p><p>A shift pattern is operated; ideally the Engineer would be able to cover the early shift (starting at 7am) or the late (ending at 6pm), as well as some weekend work.  There is flexibility on a case by case. </p><p>  </p><p>Preferably a minimum of 5 + years of relevant experience.</p></div><div class="rich-text" itemprop="description"><p>Hatstand is a global financial technology consultancy.  We specialise in three key components of financial markets:  Trading Systems and Connectivity, Data Management and<strong> </strong>Risk, Compliance and Regulation. </p><p>  </p><p>We work closely with our clients to deliver flexible, bespoke solutions that address the diverse challenges of the financial technology environment.  Our international reach allows us to successfully execute projects and managed services across the globe, with offices in London, Geneva, Dubai, New York, Hong Kong, Singapore and Sydney.   </p><p>  </p><p>We pride ourselves on our global team of highly experienced senior consultants, complemented by our unique talent management programme that provides talented IT professionals with tailored training and mentoring – the Hatstand Green Beret Programme.</p></div>